        <num>CCRP 651</num>
        <heading>651.  When defense of insanity at time of offense is available; method of trial</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 651.  When defense of insanity at time of offense is available; method of trial
When a defendant is tried upon a plea of &quot;not guilty&quot;, evidence of insanity or mental defect at the time of the offense shall not be admissible.
The defenses available under a combined plea of &quot;not guilty and not guilty by reason of insanity&quot; shall be tried together.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112673</p>
        </authorialNote>
